The '1986â87 FA Cup' was the 106th season of the world's oldest football
knockout competition, 'The Football Association Challenge Cup', or FA Cup for
short. The competition was won by Coventry City, who beat Tottenham Hotspur 3â2,
after extra-time, in the final at Wembley Stadium. It was Tottenham's only
defeat in eight finals up to that point. The tournament started in August 1986,
with non-league teams competing in the [http://www.thefa.com/facup/archives
qualifying rounds]. Clubs from the First and Second Divisions entered in the
third round.
